body:
Honestly speaking, I've taken inspiration from [RandomStringUtils](https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-lang/apidocs/org/apache/commons/lang3/RandomStringUtils.html), but I see the point about `isNumeric`.

I agree `isDigit` is a more sensible name, thanks for that @chagmed.

@NeshkaD would you mind taking this into consideration?

**Team decision**

- The following assertions will be included:

```java
assertThat(string).isAlphabetic();   // \p{Alpha}
assertThat(string).isAlphanumeric(); // \p{Alnum}
assertThat(string).isASCII();        // \p{ASCII}
assertThat(string).isHexadecimal();  // \p{XDigit}
assertThat(string).isPrintable();    // \p{Print}
assertThat(string).isVisible();      // \p{Graph}
```

- The existing `containsOnlyDigits` will not be deprecated.
